text: Ozernoye () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Ozernovsky Selsoviet in Ikryaninsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 653 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 67 km from Astrakhan, 21 km from Ikryanoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ikryaninsky District
title: Ozernoye, Astrakhan Oblast
